<TITLE> 2 killed as storm rips down billboard in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 15 (bdnews24.com)At least two people died and 10 others were injured as a sudden storm ripped down a billboard in the capital's Gulshan area on Monday. The billboard at Gulshan-1 intersection crashed down onto the street below hitting at least four people and a number of cars, officer-in-charge of Gulshan Police Station, Kamal Uddin, told bdnews24.com. Fifteen year old Saiful Islam, a fast-food shop worker, died on the spot as he emerged from his workplace to watch the storm. Three of his companions were also injured. Another injured person, the driver of a car who could not be immediately identified, was taken to the United Hospital, where he died, the police officer said. The storm, bringing severe downpours, lasted for around two hours in the late evening, hampering rush home for many city dwellers. Vehicles were forced to a halt in parts of the city due to the heavy rain and water logging. The meteorological department recorded 16 mm rainfall in Dhaka between 6-8 p.m, met officer Rasheduzzaman told bdnews24.com. He said there had been no rain anywhere in the country up to 6pm. "Sudden storms are not unusual in these days," he added. bdnews2
